# Styling Guidelines - Design System

## Theme Colors

**ALWAYS use theme colors from CSS variables. NEVER use hardcoded colors like `text-gray-900`, `bg-white`, `bg-gray-50`, etc.**

### Available Theme Colors

- **Text Colors:**
  - `text-foreground` - Primary text (replaces `text-gray-900 dark:text-white`)
  - `text-muted-foreground` - Secondary text (replaces `text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400`)
  - `text-primary` - Primary accent text
  - `text-destructive` - Error/destructive text
  - `text-warning` - Warning text
  - `text-success` - Success text

- **Background Colors:**
  - `bg-background` - Main background
  - `bg-card` - Card/container background (replaces `bg-white dark:bg-gray-800`)
  - `bg-muted` - Muted background (replaces `bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800`)
  - `bg-primary/20` - Primary with opacity
  - `bg-destructive/10` - Destructive with opacity

- **Border Colors:**
  - `border-primary/20` - Primary border (replaces `border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700`)
  - `border-border` - Default border
  - `border-destructive/30` - Destructive border

## Utility Classes

### Glass Effect
Use `.glass-effect` for modern glassmorphism styling:
```tsx
<div className="glass-effect rounded-lg p-6">
  {/* Content */}
</div>
```

### Modal/Dialog
```tsx
<div className="modal-container">
  <div className="modal-header">
    <h2 className="modal-title">Title</h2>
  </div>
  <div className="modal-content">
    {/* Content */}
  </div>
</div>
```

### Form Elements
```tsx
<label className="form-label">Label</label>
<input className="form-input" />
<select className="form-select">...</select>
<p className="form-description">Helper text</p>
```

### Cards
```tsx
<div className="card-modern">
  <div className="card-header-modern">
    <h3 className="card-title-modern">Title</h3>
    <p className="card-description-modern">Description</p>
  </div>
  {/* Content */}
</div>
```

### Buttons
```tsx
<button className="btn-primary">Primary Action</button>
<button className="btn-secondary">Secondary Action</button>
<button className="btn-destructive">Delete</button>
```

### Alerts/Messages
```tsx
<div className="alert-error">
  <p className="alert-error-text">Error message</p>
</div>
<div className="alert-warning">
  <p className="alert-warning-text">Warning message</p>
</div>
<div className="alert-success">
  <p className="alert-success-text">Success message</p>
</div>
```

## Forbidden Patterns

**DO NOT USE:**
- `text-gray-*` - Use `text-foreground` or `text-muted-foreground`
- `bg-white` or `bg-gray-*` - Use `bg-card` or `bg-background`
- `border-gray-*` - Use `border-primary/20` or `border-border`
- `dark:` variants for colors - Theme handles dark mode automatically
- Hardcoded hex/rgb colors - Use theme CSS variables

## Component Patterns

### Input Fields
Always use theme-aware styling:
```tsx
<input className="form-input" />
// OR manually:
<input className="w-full px-3 py-2 border border-primary/20 rounded-lg bg-card text-foreground focus:ring-2 focus:ring-primary focus:border-primary/50" />
```

### Cards/Containers
```tsx
<div className="card-modern">
  {/* OR manually: */}
  <div className="glass-effect rounded-lg border-primary/20">
    {/* Content */}
  </div>
</div>
```

### Headers/Sections
```tsx
<div className="glass-effect border-b border-primary/20 backdrop-blur-xl">
  <h2 className="text-lg font-semibold text-foreground">Title</h2>
  <p className="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Description</p>
</div>
```

## Base Styles

The following elements automatically use theme colors (defined in `global.css`):
- All `input`, `textarea`, `select` elements
- All `button` elements
- All elements via `border-border` and `outline-ring/50`

## Migration Checklist

When updating components:
1. ✅ Replace `text-gray-*` with `text-foreground` or `text-muted-foreground`
2. ✅ Replace `bg-white`/`bg-gray-*` with `bg-card` or `glass-effect`
3. ✅ Replace `border-gray-*` with `border-primary/20` or `border-border`
4. ✅ Remove all `dark:` color variants (theme handles it)
5. ✅ Use utility classes where possible (`.form-input`, `.card-modern`, etc.)
6. ✅ Ensure modals use `.modal-container` or `.glass-effect`
7. ✅ Ensure buttons use theme colors or utility classes

## Examples

### ❌ Bad
```tsx
<div className="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
  <h2 className="text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Title</h2>
  <p className="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Description</p>
</div>
```

### ✅ Good
```tsx
<div className="glass-effect">
  <h2 className="text-foreground">Title</h2>
  <p className="text-muted-foreground">Description</p>
</div>
```

### ❌ Bad
```tsx
<input className="w-full px-3 py-2 border border-gray-300 dark:border-gray-600 rounded-lg bg-white dark:bg-gray-700 text-gray-900 dark:text-white" />
```

### ✅ Good
